      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 1399: latestEditionId is set from pendingEditions.front(), but the loaded/current body is also taken from front() while the remaining pending editions are appended as older editions. This is only correct if the deque is guaranteed newest-first in every load path. The existing insertion uses different push directions depending on messageReceived, so out-of-order/history loading can mark the wrong edition as latest. That breaks the new guard in injectEditionOverwrites(), causing the real latest plugin bodyOverwrite to be ignored or an older overwrite to remain displayed. Sort pending editions by commit order/date before applying them, then set latestEditionId from the edition that actually provides the current body.\n```suggestion\n// Before applying pending editions, order them consistently so the current body\n// and latestEditionId always refer to the newest edition commit.\nauto\u0026 editions \u003d peditIt-\u003esecond;\nstd::sort(editions.begin(), editions.end(), [](const auto\u0026 lhs, const auto\u0026 rhs) {\n    return lhs-\u003etimestamp \u003e rhs-\u003etimestamp;\n});\nsharedCommit-\u003elatestEditionId \u003d editions.front()-\u003eid;\n```",
