      "message": "[Major] Line 1988: loadMissingBodyOverwrites() transforms every loaded TEXT message missing bodyOverwrite, including original messages that have already been edited. For edited messages, the original SwarmMessage body has been replaced with the latest edition body, while edition commits are also transformed separately. This can issue duplicate plugin work and, depending on iteration order, can overwrite the original message pluginData with a transform that is not tied to latestEditionId. Restrict original-message transforms to messages without editions, and let edition commits drive overwrites for edited messages.\n```suggestion\nconst auto isEdition \u003d msg-\u003ebody.contains(CommitKey::EDIT) \u0026\u0026 !msg-\u003ebody.at(CommitKey::EDIT).empty();\nconst auto hasEditions \u003d !msg-\u003eeditions.empty();\nif (msg-\u003etype \u003d\u003d CommitType::TEXT \u0026\u0026 !hasEditions \u0026\u0026 !msg-\u003epluginData.contains(\"bodyOverwrite\")) {\n    batch.push_back(*msg);\n} else if (msg-\u003etype \u003d\u003d CommitType::TEXT \u0026\u0026 isEdition \u0026\u0026 !msg-\u003epluginData.contains(\"bodyOverwrite\")) {\n    batch.push_back(*msg);\n}\n```",
