      "message": "[Critical] Line 2018: When the plugin returns an empty bodyOverwrite, the code stores pluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] \u003d \"\" directly and skips injectEditionOverwrites(). For edition commits this means any previous overwrite propagated to the original message is not cleared, so clients can keep showing stale overwritten text after a plugin disables or clears a transform. Use injectEditionOverwrites(transformed.id, \"\") for empty results as well so clearing follows the same propagation path.\n```suggestion\nconst auto boIt \u003d transformed.pluginData.find(\"bodyOverwrite\");\nif (boIt \u003d\u003d transformed.pluginData.end()) {\n    continue;\n}\nif (auto signalMsg \u003d injectEditionOverwrites(transformed.id, boIt-\u003esecond); !signalMsg.id.empty()) {\n    signalMap[signalMsg.id] \u003d std::move(signalMsg);\n}\n```",
